{
  "texts": [
    "This community structure is also present in dynamic graphs, but the community configurations can evolve as the graph structure changes.",
    "The identification and comprehension of dynamic community structures and their evolutionary patterns can provide a deeper comprehension of the graph and its community formations, which facilitates the prediction of potential changes in the graph.",
    "Taking social networks as an example, users with similar likes and follows can be grouped into the same interest clusters.",
    "By identifying these clusters, the system is able to recommend new connections or content that aligns with their interests.Transductive / inductive setting.",
    "In the transductive setting, the model attempts to make accurate predictions on the graph on which it was initially trained."
  ]
}